    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>Jany 18&#44; 1849</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Eq </addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Revd &#38; dear Sir</p>
			<p>For some days past I have been<lb/> very unwell The cholera attacked<lb/> me very hard but thanks to a Divine<lb/> Providence I am again restor&#39;d<lb/> to Health &#38; at your Service<lb/> I instructed my Book Keeper<lb/> to answer your Last Letter&#44; which<lb/> he informs me he did. I must here<lb/> confirm his words&#44; vz&#44; some of those<lb/> Books are not only Insured but<lb/> appear to have been used.</p>
			<p>Its strange not one of the members<lb/> of the Portuguese Congregation<lb/> seem willing to buy any of your<lb/> <sic>Preyer</sic> Books. now I presume<lb/> If there was none here they would<lb/> be forwarding their Orders to you<lb/> or elsewhere for various Books<lb/> yet here they are &#38; not a soul<lb/> needs them. I am happy to inform<lb/> you the <add>&#63;</add>etcher Books are moving<lb/> I sent <persName>Emanuel Mobile</persName> 1 Doz Four<lb/> of each price &#38; have left 7 c2.75&#8212;11 c 2 50</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>&#38; 4 c &#36;3.00&#8212;these Books will sell<lb/> here all the year round. I see them<lb/> at your Invoice price</p>
			<p>I was notified by <persName>Barnett</persName> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> &#38; a <persName>De Young</persName> &#40;not positive of the latter&#41;<lb/> that the <date>December</date> No of the<lb/> Occident did not reach them<lb/> but the <date>January</date> Number<lb/> is at hand &#38; I have waited<lb/> on the two first Gentlemen &#38;<lb/> find they are in receipt of their<lb/> number for this present<lb/> month.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I beg to return you<lb/> for my most Sincere thanks<lb/> for your notice of our Loan<lb/> on Whole Congregation will feel<lb/> themselves your Debtors. The <persName>Revd Mr Carrolina</persName> has now<lb/> been here some time endeavouring<lb/> to obtain the office of Reader to<lb/> the Portuguese Congregation<lb/> It is still expected <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> will<lb/> come but should he decline<lb/> the <persName>Revd Carrolina</persName> will not <sic>suceed</sic><lb/> He is very unpopular&#8212;</p>
			<p>I have given to <persName>Joseph Turner</persName><lb/> the Numbers 1c10 of this Volume<lb/> of the Occident. send him the</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>next number when it comes out<lb/> &#40;<date>February</date>&#41; &#38; send me the 10 numbers I give<lb/> to Him. add his name to your List<lb/> of subscribers. I will collect their money<lb/> &#38; with what I trust soon to be<lb/> enabled to send you from the sale<lb/> of your Books I will add the amount<lb/> of those subscribers I have obtained<lb/> I shall obtain all the subscribers I<lb/> possibly can &#38; now Sir I must<lb/> come to a hasty conclusion<lb/> Pardon this scrawl my Business<lb/> occupying so much of my time gives<lb/> me but a few moments to private<lb/> correspondence</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Believe me to</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">remain your</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Sincere Well Wisher</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName></p>
          
        </body>
